==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm}} {{term|growen|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang}} {{term|growan|grōwan|to grow, increase, flourish, germinate|lang=ang}}, from {{proto|Germanic|grōanan|to grow, grow green|lang=en}}, from {{proto|Indo-European|gʰreH₁-|to grow, become green|lang=en}}. Cognate with Dutch {{term|groeien||to grow|lang=nl}}, {{etyl|da|-}} and {{etyl|no|-}} {{term|gro||to grow|lang=da|lang=no}}, {{etyl|sv|-}} {{term|gro||to germinate, grow, sprout; related to {{term|gröda||crop|lang=sv|lang=sv}}}}, {{etyl|la|-}} {{term|herba||plant, herb, weed|lang=la}}. Related to [[grass]], [[green]].

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/ɡɹəʊ/}}, {{SAMPA|/gr@U/}}
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/ɡɹoʊ/}}
